@*
1. In the first row, bind the input to the date observable (requires creating a ko binding). Make the selector a date selector.
2. Display date in the p in the next row using moment.format with support for null values.
3. Turn the selector into datetime selector, the time part selector should be always displayed.
4. Turn the selector into year-month selector.
5. Back to date selector.
6. Create dateTimePickerMinDate and dateTimePickerMaxDate bindings (note: how are they created?); bind the date picker to the minDate and maxDate observables.
